{"blocks":[{"key":"6at26","text":"Add ~107 PFU of phage T4 (ATCC Strain 11303-b4) to the E. coli subculture, and ~107 PFU of phage SPO1 (ATCC Strain 27370-b1) to the B. subtilis subculture. Return the infected subcultures to the incubator, at 37 °C with shaking. Grow until the culture is cleared (around 5 h). If the culture doesn't completely clear within 5 h, you can let the infection proceed overnight.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":7,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":82,"length":1},{"style":"italic","offset":55,"length":8},{"style":"italic","offset":132,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cokdk","text":"Move the phage lysate to a 50 mL conical tube, and add ~1 mL of chloroform. Seal the tube tightly, and shake on a platform shaker for 10–30 min. Transfer to a new conical tube. Then, spin the lysate down in a centrifuge at maximum speed for 30 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b1s77","text":"Carefully pipette off the supernatant from the spun-down culture into a new 50 mL conical tube, avoiding any debris at the chloroform interface. Also avoid the chloroform. Move to a new 50 mL conical tube, and spin again at max speed for another 30 min or until supernatant is clear. Move to a new 50 mL conical tube. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ptcg","text":"To concentrate the phage lysate, we have used both PEG precipitation and a filter-concentrator based protocol. The PEG protocol requires an overnight incubation, but the filter-concentrator generally requires more hands-on time. Use whichever phage concentration protocol works best for your circumstances.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

cases.title: Filter-concentrator based phage prep
cases.description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2fgfo","text":"Alternative protocol using filter-concentrators to concentrate phage, instead of precipitation. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"c0a1n","text":"For each host, prepare a 30 mL subculture at 1:100 dilution (300 µL in 30 mL). Grow for 2 h at 37 °C in a shaking incubator. Subculture media (LB or ENB) should be supplemented with 1 mM CaCl2 and 1 mM MgCl2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":191,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":206,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8qcmo","text":"To PEG-precipitate phage, first prepare 5× PEG precipitation solution containing 2.5 M NaCl and 20% w/v PEG8000.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dntbr","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1rddp","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":24,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"c5fs","text":"5× PEG solution (500 mL)","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"9orl3","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"13it","text":"5 M NaCl stock solution – 250 mL ","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"43nb6","text":"PEG8000 – 100 g","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"22ccl","text":"DI water – to 500 mL","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"31t4o","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"32l32","text":"Stir until dissolved. Sterilize with with 0.22 µm filter. Store at room temperature.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9j86g","text":"Add PEG precipitation solution to the phage lysate to obtain a 1× concentration of 0.5 M NaCl and 4% w/v PEG8000. Mix by inverting the tube several times and refrigerate overnight at 4 °C. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"anp6s","text":"Before concentrating, we recommend filtering the supernatant with a 0.22-µM Steriflip filter (EMD Millipore SCGP00525). This can help cut down on the carry-over of host nucleic acids into the phage prep. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6qql2","text":"To concentrate the phage lysate, use a variation of the \"Phage on Tap\" method. After equilibrating a 100 kDa MWCO Amicon centrifugal filter unit (EMD Millipore UFC910024) with SM buffer (Bioworld 41920012-1), use the filter unit to concentrate the ~30 mL of phage lysate down to 0.5–3 mL. As the phage is being concentrated, use SM buffer to wash the sides of the filter. Store phage at 4 °C. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2s8pq","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1djcc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"citation","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"authors":"Bonilla N, Rojas MI, Netto Flores Cruz G, Hung SH, Rohwer F, Barr JJ","can_edit":1,"date":"1469491200","doi":"https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.2261","guid":"241267204E4111ED8EE443A92453120B","id":2060,"journal":"PeerJ","protocol_id":"0","title":"Phage on tap-a quick and efficient protocol for the preparation of bacteriophage laboratory stocks."}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"el996","text":"After the overnight incubation with PEG precipitation solution at 4 °C, pellet the PEG precipitated phage particles by centrifuging at 19,000 × g for 60 min at 4 °C. A small white pellet should form at the bottom of the 50 mL conical tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3754o","text":"Remove the supernatant, being careful not to disturb the PEG-precipitated phage pellet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"q1c6","text":"Resuspend the PEG-precipitated phage pellet in 300 µL SM buffer. Store at 4 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
